{"id": "1459555990478524569", "channel_id": "1459555990478524569", "type": 0, "author_id": "139343733714845697", "author_name": "satachan", "author_bot": false, "content": "While I know that asking for rebalance isn't really a viable thing to do because the dev team has their own priority. But I would still like to leave a note stuck to the door as a wanda enthusiast. \n\nCurrently I believe that she is incredibly easily outdone by almost every character in her niche as a counter generator. \n\nHer 4 cost card is not as powerful in the current ecosystem and generally doesnt justify the cost of using it. \n\nHer 3 cost's refund makes her viable to do dps but it doesn't really benefit wanda as much as it is right now as her job in the current meta is to generate as much counter as possible.\n\nThis means that out of her entire kit, the only reason people are using her is for her exalt, which sometimes gives good counter if you have 5 dreamlure but sometimes it doesn't do much at all. The base effect of her exalt is too weak allowing for an easy fail state for newer players.\n\nI feel like this isn't a very good spot for wanda to be in.\n\nShe wants to be the str debuffer but she loses to goliath.\n\nShe wants to be the counter generator but loses to caecus's 2 cost. \n\nShe wants to do damage but is dependent on generating counter, meaning daffodil + pandia is more viable than her in harder content. \n\nHer dreamlure mechanic is almost negligible at this point and the aliemus cap increases works against her job as a counter generator.\n\nI still enjoy using wanda and will continue to use her but I really want to at least knock on the door of my favorite developer that this long forgotten character may require some spot in the sunlight.\n\nThank you!", "timestamp": "2026-01-10T14:34:25.369000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "proud", "emoji_id": "1400771808356991057", "count": 7}, {"emoji": "approved", "emoji_id": "1356053028787982558", "count": 4}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1459555990478524569", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Possibilty of rebalancing Wanda?", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801", "1361169005435420785"]}
{"id": "1459565449954984064", "channel_id": "1459555990478524569", "type": 0, "author_id": "139343733714845697", "author_name": "satachan", "author_bot": false, "content": "Another point to make,\n\nDuring arc 1, counter was the most powerful team. But it also made the gameplay very bland and slow.\n\nIf that is the case, with the new design philosophy of a lot of the current content in morimens.\n\nWouldn't it be better to do get rid of counter entirely and rework the counter based characters into their own niche? \n\nI feel like the gameplay of counter hasn't evolved much and there is no real need to make counter be the ultra passive damage.", "timestamp": "2026-01-10T15:12:00.684000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1459555990478524569", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Possibilty of rebalancing Wanda?", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801", "1361169005435420785"]}
